Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.58,0:02:07.71,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:121580,127711}"The Miracle Worker" opened its curtain\Nwith a double cast of Maya and Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.71,0:02:12.04,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:127711,132049}The first day was successful\Nwith Ayumi's perfect acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.04,0:02:19.26,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:132049,139264}And now the second night, after Ayumi's\Noverwhelming act, Maya appears on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.09,0:02:27.06,Episode title,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:140097,147064}{\an5\pos(766,720)\fscy95\blur1\fad(700,500)}—Episode 21—\NNominated for\NBest Supporting Actress
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.73,0:02:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:151735,153445}Today is finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.44,0:02:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:153445,155155}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.44,0:02:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:155447,157949}Look at how much less of an audience is here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.94,0:02:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:157949,160827}It's because this actress\Nplaying Helen is less known.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.82,0:02:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:160827,167084}Look at this. Even most of the flowers\Nare addressed to Himekawa Utako and Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.37,0:02:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:170379,173256}Quality rather than quantity,\Nit's how much of our heart we put in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.25,0:02:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:173256,175175}Excuse me, here's a delivery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.59,0:03:00.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:177594,180305}What's wrong, Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.72,0:03:02.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:180722,182432}I'm nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.43,0:03:05.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:182432,185519}I'm afraid to be compared with Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.56,0:03:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:187562,189648}Maya!\NCome look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.64,0:03:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:189648,190732}Hurry, Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.73,0:03:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:190732,191566}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.56,0:03:14.82,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:191566,194820}{\fad(0,1500)}Ms. Kitajima Maya
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.11,0:03:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:196113,200617}Wow, look at the size of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.90,0:03:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:200909,202119}Maya, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.28,0:03:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:203286,206164}"I'm looking forward\Nto seeing your Helen."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.27,0:03:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:207273,209960}He's here!\NMr. Purple Rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.96,0:03:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:209960,213922}He's looking, somewhere in this big hall…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:213922,216007}…for my… my Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.00,0:03:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:216007,219094}Yes.\NYour Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.63,0:03:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:220637,221847}Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:221847,224015}Maya, it seems like you're calmer now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.01,0:03:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:224015,224683}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.68,0:03:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:224683,227602}I'm looking forward to your Helen as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.60,0:03:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:227602,229104}Teacher…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.10,0:03:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:229104,231440}A miracle is not something that just happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.44,0:03:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:231440,234401}You make it happen,\Nwith your own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.40,0:03:59.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:234401,239780}A miracle is something I make\Nhappen with my own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.45,0:04:08.54,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:244453,248540}"The Miracle Worker," played by\NMaya and Utako, has started.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.13,0:04:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:257132,259634}Young lady,\Nit's your day off today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.26,0:04:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:262262,263638}Please, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.43,0:04:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:264431,266767}Thank you for coming,\NMs. Sullivan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.76,0:04:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:266767,269102}This is my husband.\NThis is Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.10,0:04:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:269102,270187}Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.18,0:04:33.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:270187,273023}Mr. Purple Rose.\NI'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.02,0:04:35.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:273023,275150}I'm not scared anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.77,0:04:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:276777,280530}Since when did this country became so big?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.50,0:04:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:296505,298548}Where should I put the suitcase, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.54,0:05:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:298548,301551}Let's put it somewhere convenient for Ms. Sullivan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.55,0:05:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:301551,303512}Yes, that will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.51,0:05:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:303512,304721}Where's Helen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.72,0:05:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:304721,306848}I'll take the suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.84,0:05:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:306848,307849}No, I can carry it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.84,0:05:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:307849,309601}Oh no, I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.77,0:05:20.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:316775,320362}This girl seems so different from practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.36,0:05:22.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:320362,322739}She seems like a totally different person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.73,0:05:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:322739,323573}That's Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.57,0:05:25.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:323573,325617}Oh no, it was my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.05,0:05:48.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:343051,348098}This is it: this breath, this rhythm,\Nthe tension and the calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.09,0:05:51.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:348098,351351}The actor who can capture that,\Ncan grab the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.35,0:05:55.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:351351,355438}This girl doesn't know that yet,\Nbut her instinct does.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.98,0:06:01.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:358984,361444}She's leading.\NThis is dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.69,0:06:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:363697,366825}Here, Helen.\NLet's start with the doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.82,0:06:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:366825,370412}D·O·L·L.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.41,0:06:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:370412,372080}A doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.54,0:06:23.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:379546,383341}What happened?\NI moved from her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.34,0:06:25.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:383341,385719}She's supposed to slap me\Nin this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.46,0:06:28.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:386469,388763}What happened to Utako?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.76,0:06:30.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:388763,390181}She's taken by Maya's pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.22,0:06:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:396229,399190}Strange. I can see the darkness around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.19,0:06:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:399190,400025}The darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.02,0:06:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:400025,406239}The darkness… the kind of darkness that Helen,\Nwho was blind and deaf, was feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.23,0:06:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:406239,408575}The darkness that Helen was feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.57,0:06:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:408575,413163}There's plenty of light,\Nbut by looking at her movement…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.16,0:06:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:413163,416458}…it makes me feel blinded\Nto the things around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.16,0:07:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:418168,423798}But, her movement is not like Helen,\Nor at least not what's known to be Helen's.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.18,0:07:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:430180,435769}Just because Helen is being played\Nby a different actress makes it a whole new play.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.31,0:07:19.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:436311,439147}Maya, you're great.\NWonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.14,0:07:23.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:439147,443610}They say a play is alive,\Nbut you truly are alive now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.19,0:07:31.24,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:445195,451242}Helen and the lady teacher, Sullivan,\Nnothing was changed from the script…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.24,0:07:39.62,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:451242,459626}…but Utako was feeling that the play\Nwas going in an entirely different direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.62,0:07:43.21,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:459626,463213}The first act was finally over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.00,0:07:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:464005,467467}Are you okay, Utako?\NYou're sweating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:467467,469678}Mr. Onodera, I have a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.67,0:07:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:469678,471012}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.01,0:07:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:471012,473598}I want you to let me take control of this play.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.59,0:07:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:473598,474432}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.43,0:07:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:474432,477560}I want to fight her Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.56,0:08:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:477560,480939}No ordinary Sullivan\Ncan fight against her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.56,0:08:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:481564,484317}With her, I can not just act.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.31,0:08:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:484317,487320}I've noticed that I'm not acting, but being real.\NThis is the first time this has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.19,0:08:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:489197,490698}I'm an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.69,0:08:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:490698,493660}To make this play a success, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.86,0:08:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:494869,495953}Mr. Onodera.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.95,0:08:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:495953,497122}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.12,0:08:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:497122,500625}I'll trust you on this.\NIt's an actor's world on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.62,0:08:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:500625,501418}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.96,0:08:24.75,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:501960,504753}The second act has started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.75,0:08:29.09,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:504753,509092}Sitting in the lobby, Ayumi's heart was filled\Nwith a nervous feeling about Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.13,0:08:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:511136,512721}Please hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.72,0:08:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:512721,516182}Okay, I'll get a bunch of film,\Nand we've got to take lots of pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.68,0:08:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:516683,520729}Great, why don't we have enough film\Nat a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.72,0:08:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:520729,524733}But, this Helen and Sullivan\Nare really something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.73,0:08:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:524733,526901}I've never seen anything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.69,0:08:52.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:530697,532198}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.19,0:08:54.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:532198,534200}What did he mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.03,0:08:59.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:535035,539164}What's going on\Nbehind those doors?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.08,0:09:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:541082,541665}Rei?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.55,0:09:14.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:551551,554471}Different.\NThis is different from practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.47,0:09:16.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:554471,556306}Mrs. Himekawa Utako.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.01,0:09:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:559017,564564}Here, Helen. I want you to understand\Nthat things have names.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.56,0:09:27.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:564564,567650}Helen.\NYes, I am Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.65,0:09:31.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:567650,571654}Whatever happens or changes,\NI am Helen on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.32,0:09:43.33,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:579329,583333}The two were no longer acting,\Nbut became real.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.33,0:09:52.34,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:583333,592342}Maya became Helen, and, like her,\NUtako became Annie Sullivan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.34,0:10:01.76,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:592342,601768}Between them was a shared rhythm,\Nand they were even feeling a sense of connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.76,0:10:05.14,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:601768,605146}Finally, the climactic miracle scene came.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.14,0:10:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:605146,606815}Here, pump.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.81,0:10:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:606815,608440}No, your mom isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.44,0:10:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:608440,610944}No, pump.\NThis is water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.94,0:10:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:610944,615406}W·A·T·E·R.\NWater.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.74,0:10:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:615740,617867}This is its name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.67,0:10:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:635677,636845}Helen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.15,0:10:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:650150,653319}Wa… ter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.78,0:11:08.54,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:662787,668543}The battle between Sullivan and Helen,\NUtako and Maya, was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.71,0:11:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:671713,674424}It's not over yet, it's a curtain call.\NOpen it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.98,0:11:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:694986,696738}Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.73,0:11:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:696738,699324}She didn't even kiss\Nher own daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.62,0:11:55.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:709626,715298}Maya. You inspire me\Nto keep up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.21,0:12:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:718218,721638}Mr. Purple Rose, did you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.63,0:12:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:721638,723306}My Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.30,0:12:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:723306,727602}I might have given up\Nwithout your encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.39,0:12:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:733399,735318}Who?\NWho's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:22.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:737111,742700}Is it… Mr. Purple Rose?
Comment: 0,0:12:22.69,0:12:22.69,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:742699,742699}Eyecatch
Comment: 0,0:12:26.41,0:12:26.41,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:746411,746411}#Eyecatch
Comment: 0,0:12:29.41,0:12:29.41,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:749415,749415}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.79,0:12:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:753795,756339}Mr. Purple Rose,\NI know you are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.67,0:12:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:760677,762804}Hello there, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.80,0:12:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:762804,763805}You.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.80,0:12:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:763805,766349}Are you looking\Nfor someone in a hurry?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.34,0:12:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:766349,767767}I… I…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.76,0:12:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:767767,769852}He must be important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.39,0:12:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:770395,772230}I know it's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.23,0:12:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:772230,773982}You really hate me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.98,0:12:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:773982,777277}When can you stop\Nmaking that face?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.27,0:13:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:779279,782490}The moment you see me…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.49,0:13:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:782490,785326}…you act as if you've seen\Na cockroach, centipede, or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.21,0:13:18.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:796212,798214}Kitajima Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.96,0:13:25.22,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:799966,805221}Maya and Utako's acting has received more\Nand more attention as the play continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.22,0:13:29.60,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:805221,809600}Ayumi's acting was\Nalso acclaimed by the critics…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.60,0:13:35.14,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:809600,815148}…but with Maya, there was an unknown and\Nunpredictable element that attracted the crowds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.14,0:13:40.57,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:815148,820570}When Maya and Utako were on stage,\Ntheir in sync acts had no scripts or rehearsal…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.57,0:13:44.82,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:820570,824824}…and it was different every time they played.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.07,0:13:49.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:826075,829620}Mr. Purple Rose, Mother…\Nplease watch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.62,0:13:51.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:829620,831622}Can you hear that applause?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.58,0:13:55.50,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:833583,835501}Fukui Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.87,0:13:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:835877,838463}I hear it, I heart it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.46,0:14:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:838463,841507}I hear the applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.50,0:14:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:841507,843551}How are you feeling, Haru?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.55,0:14:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:843551,844469}Oh, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.46,0:14:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:844469,847013}You seem well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.01,0:14:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:847013,850058}All thanks to you, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.05,0:14:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:850058,853936}To take care of me with no money or family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.93,0:14:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:853936,856606}Oh, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.60,0:14:22.07,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:856606,862070}Haru was taken to a hospital in Nagano\Nafter she was found passed out on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.07,0:14:26.06,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:862070,866066}She had lost her eyesight\Nfrom malnutrition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.49,0:14:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:866491,869410}Hmm?\NWhat's this scrap of paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.41,0:14:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:869410,870495}It's my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.49,0:14:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:870495,871829}Your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.82,0:14:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:871829,874123}She's my only daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.12,0:14:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:874123,878419}She's 16 now.\NShe loves to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.41,0:14:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:878419,885802}She ran away to be an actress, and I found\Nher picture in a magazine for a play she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:885802,890430}I know it was a tiny role, but look!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.68,0:14:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:891682,894268}Isn't she pretty?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.26,0:14:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:894268,896729}Oh, what a pretty girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.72,0:14:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:896729,899190}I'll be looking out for her in magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.69,0:15:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:900691,903820}Was that okay, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.82,0:15:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:903820,907323}You couldn't even see her face on that paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.32,0:15:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:907323,911035}Besides, you don't even know if she even exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.03,0:15:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:911035,916207}Shh. I know, but it's\Nthe best medicine for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.70,0:15:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:916707,918126}Maya…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.58,0:15:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919585,922380}I hear the applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.38,0:15:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:922380,924298}Your mother hears it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.29,0:15:25.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:924298,925716}Mother…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.71,0:15:28.13,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:925716,928136}"The Miracle Worker," which received\Ngreat press coverage…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.13,0:15:31.47,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:928136,931472}…finally came to the last night\Nwith a heated audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.47,0:15:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:931472,933683}Please, this is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.68,0:15:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:933683,935560}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.39,0:15:40.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:938396,940064}A purple rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.94,0:15:46.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:943943,946487}He's here, somewhere in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:48.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:946487,948072}Mr. Purple Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.75,0:16:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:959750,963963}He's somewhere in here.\NI have to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.96,0:16:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:963963,966424}Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.09,0:16:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:970094,972013}Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.01,0:16:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:972013,976309}Did anyone see who threw\Nthis purple rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.30,0:16:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:976309,978394}That's the girl who played Helen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.39,0:16:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:978394,982190}Please, I want to find the man\Nwith the purple rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.19,0:16:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:982190,983566}There's Helen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.56,0:16:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:983566,984650}I loved your Helen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.65,0:16:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:984650,986319}I came to see you five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.31,0:16:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:986319,989030}Please let me through!\NExcuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.03,0:16:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:989030,991866}I need to get through!\NExcuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.40,0:16:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:992408,993743}Please sign my book!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.74,0:16:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:995745,997704}Please…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.29,0:16:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004295,1005755}Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.51,0:16:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1012512,1014013}M-Mr. Hayami.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.01,0:16:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1014013,1015139}Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.64,0:17:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1018643,1020685}Are you okay, Mr. Masumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.68,0:17:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1020685,1022813}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.81,0:17:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1022813,1024982}It just hit my shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.90,0:17:12.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1029904,1032406}Why did he… for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.40,0:17:14.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1032406,1034825}I thought he hated me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.53,0:17:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1035535,1037286}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.28,0:17:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1037286,1038329}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.54,0:17:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1044543,1047296}I… I misunderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.29,0:17:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1047296,1050925}You might be a nice person, but I…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.42,0:17:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1052426,1054971}Thank you for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.97,0:17:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1054971,1056556}For you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.43,0:17:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1059433,1062728}I can't let our product be injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.72,0:17:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1062728,1066440}The play has ended,\Nbut we still have two extra nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.40,0:17:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1069402,1071821}That's the way it is, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1071821,1073823}D-Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.82,0:17:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1073823,1079745}Until this play is over,\NI won't be sick or injured!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.63,0:18:19.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1094635,1099098}He's always like that, a cold man.\NAlways.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.09,0:18:22.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1099098,1102935}He only cares about this theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.93,0:18:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1102935,1105021}Are you Kitajima Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.81,0:18:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1106814,1109567}Yes, I am. But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.56,0:18:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1109567,1113696}Just for twenty minutes,\Nin a coffee shop down the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.69,0:18:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1113696,1117867}We were impressed\Nwith your talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.16,0:18:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1120161,1123122}What? The main role?\NFor me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.12,0:18:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1123122,1125041}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.04,0:18:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1125041,1129587}If you come to our studio,\Nwe have TV shows, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.58,0:18:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1129587,1134383}Yeah, as a start, how about\Na main role in this play.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.38,0:18:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1134383,1136177}Me for the main role?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.17,0:18:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1136177,1138012}It's not a bad story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.01,0:18:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138012,1139347}You can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.35,0:19:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1149357,1151233}I'll take the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.23,0:19:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1151233,1153319}Really?\NThen let's hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.32,0:19:19.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1156322,1159950}Oh shit, that's Hayami Masumi\Nfrom Metropolitan Entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.36,0:19:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1160368,1162578}E-Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.37,0:19:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1163371,1165915}I don't have anything to do with\NMetropolitan Entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.12,0:19:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1171128,1172838}You are so terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.75,0:19:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1173756,1176884}I was about to get the main role.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.88,0:19:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1176884,1180721}What right do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.72,0:19:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1180721,1182723}Always getting in my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.72,0:19:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1182723,1184809}Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.80,0:19:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1184809,1186977}Don't just jump\Nonto any good stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.97,0:19:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1186977,1192108}They were scouts\Nfrom a B-class production.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.10,0:19:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1192108,1198197}If you get involved with them,\Nyou'll look like a second class actress, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.19,0:20:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1198197,1201575}Remember that,\Nif you want to become a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.57,0:20:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1201575,1204578}It's my decision.\NPlease leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.57,0:20:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1204578,1210126}Was it your dream to become\Na second class actress?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.12,0:20:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1210126,1211794}Was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.79,0:20:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1214797,1219217}I thought you'd become an actress\Nwho'd make your mother proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.17,0:20:21.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1220177,1221178}Mother…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.60,0:20:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1229603,1231564}Uhh, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.56,0:20:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1231564,1235317}Watch your act, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.31,0:20:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1235317,1239905}You've been nominated for Best Supporting Actress\Nby the Academy Awards Stage Drama Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.90,0:20:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1239905,1241532}Best Supporting Actress?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.53,0:20:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1241532,1244326}You are the favorite one, at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.32,0:20:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1244326,1246162}See you at the Academy Awards.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.50,0:20:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1253502,1255087}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.08,0:20:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1255087,1259258}I've been nominated\Nfor Best Supporting Actress?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.17,0:21:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1260176,1262011}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.01,0:21:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1262011,1265181}Yes.\NThank you for calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.47,0:21:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1266474,1272438}Oh, young lady, you've been\Nnominated for an Academy Award?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.93,0:21:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1272938,1276400}Young lady,\Nyou don't look so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.44,0:21:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1277443,1279278}Young lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.27,0:21:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1279278,1282615}I'm not the only nominee.\NThere are five.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.61,0:21:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1282615,1286952}The favored nominee is that girl,\NKitajima Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.95,0:21:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1286952,1291248}Don't misunderstand,\NI don't care about the award.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.24,0:21:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1291248,1295586}But the public has chosen her as the best actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.58,0:21:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1295586,1298214}It must be a mistake, young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.21,0:21:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1298214,1301342}It's only natural that you will get the award.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.92,0:21:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1302927,1306263}Mama… never kissed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1308307,1311977}I did all I can,\Nand I don't have any regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.97,0:21:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1311977,1313979}I played Helen\Nas perfect as I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.97,0:21:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1313979,1315523}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.52,0:22:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1315523,1321862}All the critics said\Nhow perfect your acting was.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.86,0:22:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1321862,1326033}But Mama has seen more potential\Nin her as an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.03,0:22:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1326033,1327701}Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.70,0:22:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1327701,1329620}That's why she kissed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.62,0:22:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1329620,1330830}Young lady…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.49,0:22:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1332498,1335209}I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.20,0:22:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1335209,1338754}What made her the better actress?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.75,0:22:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1338754,1341256}What's the difference between her and I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.17,0:22:27.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1345177,1347054}I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.05,0:22:29.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1347054,1349639}I'm the favored candidate?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:32.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1351016,1352351}I can't believe it…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.77,0:22:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1354770,1355604}Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.44,0:22:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1358440,1362069}Mother…!
Comment: 0,0:22:51.37,0:22:51.37,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1371370,1371370}Ending
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.58,0:23:04.71,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1378586,1384716}{\blur3}It is lonely by myself…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.71,0:23:10.80,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1384716,1390806}{\blur3}…and I almost stumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.80,0:23:22.81,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1390806,1402816}{\blur3}Somewhere calls me here,\Njust like a whisper in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.81,0:23:34.95,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1402816,1414956}{\blur3}Purple light, shining down\Non the horizon…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.95,0:23:40.83,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1414956,1420836}{\blur3}…more surer than words…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.83,0:23:46.96,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1420836,1426966}{\blur3}…telling us gently…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.96,0:23:53.05,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1426966,1433056}{\blur3}…that we'll meet\Neach other someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.05,0:23:59.14,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1433056,1439146}{\blur3}Of course you can\Nfly from far away…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.14,0:24:05.15,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1439146,1445156}{\blur3}…for the dream\Non my cheek…
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.15,0:24:11.11,Ending alt,[karaoke],0,0,0,,{TIME:1445156,1451116}{\blur3\fad(0,500)}…belongs to you.
